The paper deals with the problem of efficiently answering reachability queries over views of provenance graphs, which are commonly used in databases and data management systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel view-adaptive dynamic labeling scheme, which involves data structures and algorithms for efficient query evaluation, suggesting that it could be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of recursion in workflows, which is a common feature in software engineering and programming languages, indicating that it could be relevant to cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
